Damage Types

In RampartRPG any type of damage can be categorized into two separate types with respect to their sources:

1) Physical Damage: Damage which occurs as a result of a physical force or another force of nature:
A sword cleaving someone in two, an arrow piercing a person, someone burning from being thrown into a campfire etc.

2) Magical Damage Damage which occurs as a result of spells, magical abilities, magical creatures or objects enchanted with magical properties:
A fireball spell hitting a target, a magical sword slashing an opponent etc.

The source of the damage is the ultimate arbiter of its type as in:
Spells always do magical damage unless its specifically stated otherwise,
And all physical sources of damage be it weapons, enviromental objects or players themselves always do physical damage unless its stated otherwise.
Spells can cause weapons to be enchanted letting them to magical damage instead of physical damage.
Spells can also cause enviromental effects which trigger physical damage in the cases where its unclear the GM should pick one and stick to it.

Creatures can have a resistence or an immunity to a one or both of these damages albeit they are are rare.
Resistance: If a creature is resistant to a certain type of damage hitting them with that damage causes it to deal half damage. The damage is halved after damage absorption is calculated.
Immunity: Creatures which are immune to a certain type of damage do not take any damage from hits dealing this type of damage.

Certain spells, abilites or items may grant resistances or immunites to a character.
Since resistances and immunities completely change the nature of a battle its advised to use them sparingly.
